thread.title_full: Griesemer's saves help Rustin top Henderson

title: Griesemer's saves help Rustin top Henderson
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Little did she know that her 40 minutes - the final 40 minutes of play - would be pivotal for her team in a victory over its cross-division Ches-Mont League rival. 
Griesemer's big-time effort for the Golden Knights (12-2, 9-1) began 12 minutes into the second half, when the Warriors (13-2, 10-1) were awarded a penalty kick. 
Griesemer admitted to not having any "idea where [the shooter] was going." 
"I just kind of react to the shot. I try to see where they kick it and do my best to get there," Griesemer said. "I'm not very successful most of the time, but tonight I got lucky. That might be the only PK I've saved in a game. 
"I'm just trying to get inside the kicker's head and knock her off her game a little bit," she added. "I guess it worked." 
It wasn't just the penalty stop though, as Griesemer was peppered by shots from a determined Henderson squad. She stood firm, making eight saves, including a few key stops down the stretch. 
Her teammates rewarded her hard work. Kendall Ammerman's effort earned a corner kick with 3 minutes, 20 seconds remaining. 
Cassie Cheeseman took the corner from the left side. She hit it high and curved it into the net, fooling the keeper. The placement and pace were spot-on. 
Griesemer began the game in her sweats, cheering on her teammates. 
After her big second half, her teammates were the ones cheering for her. 
West Chester Rustin 0 1 - 1 
West Chester Henderson 0 0 - 0
